AKURE – National President, Nigeria Association of Chambers of Commerce, Industry Mines and Agriculture (NACCIMA), Ide John Udeagbala has tasked the women wing of the chambers on need for them to be on top of the game in business development. He gave the advice during the induction of national executives and state coordinators of NACCIMA Business Women Organization (NAWORG), the women wing of the chambers. Udeagbala, appreciated women members for their unfailing commitment towards the growth of NACCIMA, promised to support the full development of NAWORG. APEDETT 2022 Investments Conference: We Will Adopt Malaysian,… ETI Pays Dividend In US$, Won’t The Scarcity Of FX In Nigeria… Declaring open the event at LCCI Lagos, last Thursday, the National Chairperson of NAWORG, Hajia Aisha Abubakar solicited support for the group, saying the women were able and capable of accomplishing leadership and business development. The guest speaker, Mrs. Nneka Okekearu in her presentation noted that emphasised that NAWORG members must be intelligent emotionally, communicate effectively and have foresight for successful business. One of the state coordinators inducted, Dr.(Mrs.) Adefunmilola Williams-Daudu, who is the coordinator, Ondo State chapter of NAWORG, explained that the organization focused on facilitating trade among women in the state, the country, ECOWAS sub-region and across the world. She stated that part of NAWORG’s roles included sensitization and educating women in business at the grassroots to participate in commerce and governance. Dr.(Mrs.) Williams-Daudu described the induction as an impetus for the national executives and state coordinators to hit the ground running.